{
  "texts": [
    "Results for other models show similar trends (see App.",
    "We first verify that, as expected, model performance (Fig. 2a) substantially improves with scale, with instruction tuning and with the number of demonstrations.",
    "We then consider the two bias metrics-RSD (Fig. 2b) and BiasScore (Fig.",
    "We observe that label bias is substantial across most evaluated settings: When prompted with two or no demonstrations, all models obtain high RSD values of 0.6 or more, with base models obtaining even higher values around 0.9.",
    "This implies a widespread disparity in model performance across classes in many of the evaluated tasks, and indicates that for most tasks, models primarily succeed on instances of certain classes, while consistently failing on others."
  ]
}